BEIJING, Oct. 30 (Xinhua) -- The latest James Bond film "No Time to Die" that hit theaters in China on Friday made it to the top of the box office chart on the first day of screening, data from the China Movie Data Information Network showed Saturday. This 25th installment in the Bond franchise is Daniel Craig's fifth and final film in the role of a British spy. It pocketed 49.5 million yuan (about 7.7 million U.S. dollars) on Friday. War epic film "The Battle at Lake Changjin" moved to the second spot on the chart, raking in a revenue of 28.1 million yuan on Friday, after staying on the top for nearly a month with a gross box office taking of 5.4 billion yuan. The Chinese production was followed by "Dune," a British sci-fi film adapted from an eponymous novel written by Frank Herbert, which finished the day with an earning of 6.4 million yuan. Enditem